name: Rajeev Masand
text: @CcVoltaire @nagashwin7 I understand. And respect. I guess that‚Äôs the beauty of films. We can agree to disagree, we can all feel differently abt the same film :) Can‚Äôt argue with your facts bec I didn‚Äôt know enough abt her. But I was very fulfilled by the film.

name: Rajeev Masand
text: @CcVoltaire @nagashwin7 5...I respect your opinion entirely but don‚Äôt entirely agree. I can fully see and appreciate that you feel strongly about her and knew so much abt her but I think a film has certain limitations that a book doesn‚Äôt. I think this film captures the essence of her very big life.
location: Place(_api=<tweepy.api.API object at 0x000002189AF1E5F8>, id='7929cea6bd5b32bd', url='https://api.twitter.com/1.1/geo/id/7929cea6bd5b32bd.json', place_type='city', name='Mumbai', full_name='Mumbai, India', country_code='IN', country='India', contained_within=[], bounding_box=BoundingBox(_api=<tweepy.api.API object at 0x000002189AF1E5F8>, type='Polygon', coordinates=[[[72.74484, 18.845343], [73.003648, 18.845343], [73.003648, 19.502937], [72.74484, 19.502937]]]), attributes={})

name: Rajeev Masand
text: @CcVoltaire @nagashwin7 4...For me it is one of the most extraordinary biopics I have seen. Gave me such a solid sense of the person. I think it balanced her on screen/off screen lives quite well. I don‚Äôt agree that the recreated songs were an indulgence. I can see how it was a film nerd‚Äôs hat-doff....
location: Place(_api=<tweepy.api.API object at 0x000002189AF1E5F8>, id='7929cea6bd5b32bd', url='https://api.twitter.com/1.1/geo/id/7929cea6bd5b32bd.json', place_type='city', name='Mumbai', full_name='Mumbai, India', country_code='IN', country='India', contained_within=[], bounding_box=BoundingBox(_api=<tweepy.api.API object at 0x000002189AF1E5F8>, type='Polygon', coordinates=[[[72.74484, 18.845343], [73.003648, 18.845343], [73.003648, 19.502937], [72.74484, 19.502937]]]), attributes={})

name: Rajeev Masand
text: @CcVoltaire @nagashwin7 3...Of course the studio scene with chakrapani was a Kagaz ke phool tribute. Your other points - I didn‚Äôt know a lot abt her but the film gave me a v good sense of her. Even if some of the points you make are correct, one has to understand that a film can only pack in so much...

name: Rajeev Masand
text: @CcVoltaire @nagashwin7 2...that  she did better than him gives a sense of how she frequently overshadowed her costars. I don‚Äôt think the film shies away from revealing gemini‚Äôs character but it was through her eyes and she clearly had feelings for him even after they separated...

text: @CcVoltaire @nagashwin7 1. Thank you for taking the trouble to write in such detail. I don‚Äôt think the film failed to show her range as an artiste. The scene in which she offers to cry on cue, and as many tears as required was evidence. Plus the maya bazar song and ranga rao telling her...

text: @rishabgautam @CNNnews18 Theres no right or wrong. This isnt mathematics where there is only 1 correct answer to a sum. This is abt emotion, how a film resonates (or doesnt) with you. name: Rajeev Masand
text: @rishabgautam @CNNnews18 Also ALL films are made with a lot of passion and hard work. Even the ones that turn out to be awful. But that can‚Äôt weigh in on a critic while reviewing. name: Rajeev Masand
text: @rishabgautam @CNNnews18 The audience is not one person. Best not to generalize. For every person that likes a film, I‚Äôll show you two that don‚Äôt. name: Rajeev Masand
text: Watched #AStarIsBorn at @zurichfilmfest. Formula stuff, really nicely done. Lady Gaga is very good but it‚Äôs Bradley Cooper who‚Äôs terrific. Good luck trying to get the songs out of your head.

name: Rajeev Masand
text: Watched #LifeItself at @zurichfilmfest. All cinema is manipulative, agreed. But this felt like a pair of hands wrapped around my neck trying to squeeze out a lump. Yeeesh! Great cast wasted. Dan Fogelman‚Äôs This Is Us-style multi-generation interlinked narrative is getting tiring.

name: Rajeev Masand
text: Watched #FirstMan at @zurichfilmfest today. Dazzling, unsentimental & solid, robust filmmaking. Moon landing sequence done sparsely yet so effective. Best scene though - night before Neil Armstrong leaves for mission, a chat with his sons to prepare for all eventualities.

name: Rajeev Masand
text: @Noumit It‚Äôs not a question of personal choice. It‚Äôs abt what language publication or channel one works at. I used to work for a Hindi channel and routinely reviewed films/conducted interviews in Hindi. But at an Eng language channel it has to be in Eng. Thank you for understanding :)

name: Rajeev Masand
text: @Noumit I work for an Eng news channel so my interviews have to be in Eng. When I worked for a Hindi channel, I did them in Hindi. As simple as that. Also there are lots of good journalists doing interviews and reviews in Hindi. Read/Watch them.

text: Last film for me at #Berlinale2018 - the #StevenSoderbergh directed #Unsane. Creepy, tense, batshit crazy finale. Shot entirely on an iPhone to great results. Claire Foy is the real deal.

name: Rajeev Masand
text: @akshayerathi In a perfect world, one determines who is bigger than whom when the playing field is even. Thats not the case in the film business. And most businesses to be honest. Till then I suppose these flawed metrics will be employed.

name: Rajeev Masand
text: @akshayerathi Not sure 280 characters are enough to explain how deep rooted this problem is. It‚Äôs never been an even playing field, always been tilted in favor of men. This is not a Bollywood problem, this is a huge sociological problem. The biases are appalling and need to be addressed.

name: Rajeev Masand
text: @akshayerathi Akshaye, it IS a gender issue. They wouldn‚Äôt have used that word if it was a male star. And we‚Äôre talking abt a dance performance at an awards show. I think Priyanka is as good if not better than male stars as a live performer. Why should she not be paid as much?
